txt.en: 'A town is just a collection of buildings until there are people living there that call it home: men, women, and children walking through the streets, going to work, laughing and dancing, living their lives. Without that, this place is naught but boards stacked up in piles.'
'Hytbold is one step closer to being rebuilt and restored.'
There is much work to do to rebuild the town of Hytbold.
